  subhead="It is 9am on a Thursday in March — the first week of the new plate registrations. You are at a 1970s semi in Grove — the consumer unit is isolated, the old MK board removed, and a new Hager RCBO consumer unit being wired. The 10mm² SWA runs from the new board through a core-drilled hole in the kitchen wall, along the side passage in surface-mounted mini trunking, around the corner, and terminates at the Easee One isolator on the front wall. The earth rod drove yesterday — 8 ohms, well within tolerance for the TT system. You are wiring the seventh of twelve circuits back onto the new board — ring final, lighting, cooker, shower, immersion, boiler, and now the EV 32A RCBO. Five calls between 8am and noon. Your phone is on the worktop. The consumer unit is open and live testing imminent. Without Missed Call Text Back, three voicemails — 'need a charger quote', 'my charger has stopped working', 'calling about the workplace quote you gave us' — two hang-ups. With it, all five receive texts within seconds. The first replies at 9:20am: 'Hello — we run a chain of four dental practices across south Oxfordshire. We are transitioning our company pool vehicles to electric — eight Hyundai Kona Electrics — and we need chargers at each practice. Two chargers per practice, so eight total. They need to work with our fleet management app for reporting. Three practices have car parks but one is in a terraced high street location with rear access only. All single-phase supplies. We also want the Workplace Charging Scheme grant applied for each socket. Can you survey all four practices? The vehicles arrive in eight weeks.' At noon the board is complete. Five leads on your dashboard — including the four-dental-practice fleet charger programme."
  scenario="It is 2pm on a scorching September Saturday. You have been installing a Zappi v2 in combination with a Myenergi Eddi hot water diverter at a property in Charlbury since 8am — the homeowner has twelve solar panels, a GivEnergy Gen3 inverter, and wants excess solar to charge the BMW iX3 during the day via the Zappi in ECO+ mode and heat the immersion tank via the Eddi when the car is absent. The Myenergi hub connects both devices, the CT clamp monitors grid import/export at the meter tails, and the system prioritises EV charging over hot water over export. Six missed calls between 8am and 2pm. Without Missed Call Text Back, you descend the ladder to six unknowns. With Missed Call Text Back, all six received texts. Reply one: 'homeowner Abingdon — MG4 arriving next month, want Ohme charger, have solar panels.' Reply two: 'hotel manager Burford — four destination chargers for guests, need by Easter.' Reply three: 'developer Carterton — phase two, twenty-eight plots need per-plot EV pre-wire.' Reply four: 'homeowner Eynsham — Zappi earth fault keeps tripping, installed by another firm.' Reply five: 'school bursar Witney — want staff car park chargers, six points, WCS grant.' Reply six: 'fleet manager Didcot — twenty electric vans arriving January, need depot infrastructure.' Six leads. Saturday evening you triage — the Burford hotel Easter deadline and the Didcot depot first."
